EDP-Energias, Santander, Telefonica: Iberian Equity Preview

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-02-15T07:48:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/edp-energias-de-portugal-telefonica-iberian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Spain and Portugal trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses, and share prices are from the
previous close.  Spain’s  IBEX 35 Index  retreated 0.3 percent to 10,774.70.
Portugal’s  PSI-20 Index  climbed 0.5 percent to 8,008.87.  Spanish stocks:    Banco Santander SA  (SAN SM): Spain’s biggest lender and
Banco Espanol de Credito SA (BTO SM) will bid for Spanish
savings banks to increase their market share, Cinco Dias
reported, citing Santander Chairman Emilio Botin. Santander and
Banesto will bid for savings banks as long as the price isn’t
too high, the newspaper said, citing remarks by Botin on Feb. 4
at a convention for bank executives. Santander shares dropped
0.9 percent to 8.76 euros. Banesto shares dropped 2.5 percent to
6.13 euros.    Iberdrola Renovables SA  (IBR SM): The clean-power unit of
Iberdrola SA was cut to “neutral” from “buy” at UBS AG. The
shares slumped 3.3 percent to 2.73 euros.    Telefonica SA  (TEF SM): Andre Krause, chief financial
officer of Telefonica’s German unit, is scheduled to speak at
the Mobile World Congress in Barcelona. The shares slipped 0.3
percent to 18.28 euros.  Portuguese stocks:  EDP-Energias de Portugal SA (EDP PL): Portugal’s biggest
power company said AllianceBernstein LP bought about 6.19
million of its shares in the market on Feb. 2, raising its stake
in the utility to 2.09 percent, according to a statement on the
website of Portugal’s Securities Market Commission. The shares
advanced 0.5 percent to close at 2.82 euros before the
announcement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
